Sjors, President of the Rebbel-Club; Eighty-nine new happy stories.

No issues of Sjors were released during World War II. This first new one came about two years after the end of the war in 1947. It's a partial re-issue of Sjors, voorzitter van de Rebellenclub #3 - Negen en tachtig nieuwe vrolijke vertellijngen.

deck: Adaptation of the Ginsberg poem, in graphic novel form.
description:
First published in 1956, Allen Ginsberg's "Howl" is a prophetic masterpiece--an epic raging against dehumanizing society that overcame censorship trials and obscenity charges to become one of the most widely read poems of the century.â

Now a major motion picture, starring James Franco, Howl was directed by two-time Academy Award-winners Rob Epstein & Jeffrey Friedman, who hired Eric Drooker to animate the poem. Howl: A Graphic Novel visualizes the poem--stanza by stanza--with full color animation art Drooker designed for the film.
name: GN

description:
It is a time of great unrest. A lone ninja wandering in search of his lifeâs path unexpectedly finds his destiny when he crosses paths with a shrine maiden escaping a terrible fire that was intended to kill everyone at her temple. Together they find they are part of a much larger purpose, as fate brings them into the fold of warlord Sanada Yukimura who is gathering ten of the bravest he can find. Ten who will not only bring him victory, but become the stuff of legends. Kairi Shimotsuki brings an exciting tale of action and intrigue based upon the Edo era legend of the Sanada Ten Braves.
